<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1173,1343]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1245,1271]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Biology.</emphasis>
Reared from round and pubescent galls on the leaf midrib of 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1046,1245,1271]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gilva">
<emphasis box="[958,1046,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. gilva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[1116,1303,1245,1271]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cyclobalanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1303,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Cyclobalanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z." pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref52592" refString="Schweger, S., Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z. (2015 b) New species of cynipid inquilines of the genus Saphonecrus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from the Eastern Palaearctic, with a re-appraisal of known species world-wide. Zootaxa, 4054 (1), 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4054.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Schwéger 
<emphasis box="[151,199,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2015b
</bibRefCitation>
) and undetermined galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[597,767,1281,1307]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stewardiana">
<emphasis box="[597,767,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. stewardiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[839,1026,1281,1307]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cyclobalanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[839,1026,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Cyclobalanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[1049,1328,1281,1307]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref46786" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 b) A taxonomic review of the gall wasp genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer and other oak cynipid inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) from mainland China, with updated keys to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Zoological Studies, 60 (10), 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.6620 / ZS. 2021.60 - 10" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[1192,1240,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2021b
</bibRefCitation>
). The gall inducers have yet to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
